1. *Ručka* je pala na pod. (The handle fell on the floor.)
2. Izvukao sam novčanik iz *ručke* torbe. (I pulled out my wallet from the handle of my bag.)
3. Daj mi *ručku* za otvaranje konzerve. (Give me the handle for opening the can.)
4. Zatvori *ručku* vrata kada izađeš. (Close the door handle when you leave.)
5. *Ručka* od oraha je izuzetno tvrda. (The handle made of walnut is extremely hard.)
6. Gde su mi *ručke* za jogurt? (Where are my yogurt handles?)
7. Završio sam projektovanje *ručke* za bicikl. (I finished designing the handlebar for a bicycle.)
8. Promenio sam *ručke* na svojoj gitaru. (I changed the handles on my guitar.)
9. Uključila sam *ručku* za grejanje. (I turned on the heating handle.)
10. Dečak je pričvrstio *ručku* na svoju drvenu lutku. (The boy attached the handle to his wooden doll.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "ručka" can have multiple meanings, such as handle, grip, knob, lever, handgrip, handhold, etc. Therefore, the translations of the sentences may vary depending on the context.